03/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Pirate Party of Serbia was promoted at an event in Belgrade on Monday (August 2nd).
Amelia Andersdotter of Sweden's Pirate Party attended, and said that Serbia could become a player on the global marker using its IT knowledge and telecommunications.
Serbia's Pirate Party will strive to reform rules regarding copyright and patents.
Founder Aleksandar Blagojevic said that the party's aim is to defend citizens' rights.
(Beta, B92 - 02/08/10)
